SUMMARY:2026 Spring Plant Festival
LOCATION:12210 USF Pine Drive Tampa \, FL 33612 United States
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a two-day celebration of all things plants! The US
 F Botanical Gardens Spring Plant Festival brings together over 40 local gr
 owers\, rare and native plants\, artisan goods\, food trucks and family-fr
 iendly activities  all in the beautiful setting of the USF Botanical Garde
 ns. Whether youre an experienced gardener or just getting your hands dirty
  for the first time\, this is the perfect place to discover your next favo
 rite plant  and get expert advice while youre at it. Tickets Discounted ti
 ckets are available now for pre-sale  secure your spot today and skip the 
 line! Purchase Tickets Here Tickets will be sold at the door for 10 Festiv
 al Highlights Shop a wide selection of rare\, native\, and exotic plants C
 onnect with local growers and plant experts Browse artisan vendors with ha
 ndcrafted goods Enjoy delicious eats from Tampas best food trucks Bring yo
 ur furry friend (on a leash) Create memories with fun activities for the w
 hole family Event Details Dates: April 11  12\, 2026 Time: 9 a.m.  3 p.m. 
 Membership early access at 8:30 a.m . Location: USF Botanical Gardens 1221
 0 USF Pine Drive\, Tampa\, FL 33612 Accessibility Visitor parking availabl
 e on-site  Handicap parking available along USF Pine Drive Plant Pick-Up A
 rea located next to the admission tents Please note: The BullRunner shuttl
 e will NOT be in service during the event Accessibility Accommodations or 
 Questions? The USF Botanical Gardens is committed to providing an inclusiv
 e and accessible experience for all guests. If you require reasonable acco
 mmodations or have any questions\, please contact us at botanicalgardensus
 f.edu (mailto:cas-rsvpusf.edu?subjectFall20Festival20Accessibility20Concer
 ns) before the event. All dogs and small pets on leashes are welcome! Dont
  miss this beloved spring tradition! Come for the plants  stay for the peo
 ple\, food\, and inspiration. \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/18
 7631
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/187631
END:VEVENT
